0747, 322, 527, 3652, 382, 364, 1365, 13, 51364], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1119408536313185, "compression_ratio": 1.7307692307692308, "no_speech_prob": 0.010756919160485268}, {"id": 42, "seek": 13004, "start": 150.04, "end": 154.04, "text": " But there's very few organizations that I've ever come across that will, for instance,", "tokens": [51364, 583, 456, 311, 588, 1326, 6150, 300, 286, 600, 1562, 808, 2108, 300, 486, 11, 337, 5197, 11, 51564], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1119408536313185, "compression_ratio": 1.7307692307692308, "no_speech_prob": 0.010756919160485268}, {"id": 43, "seek": 13004, "start": 154.04, "end": 158.04, "text": " look at a new server that's arrived, just look at every chip on that motherboard", "tokens": [51564, 574, 412, 257, 777, 7154, 300, 311, 6678, 11, 445, 574, 412, 633, 11409, 322, 300, 32916, 51764], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1119408536313185, "compression_ratio": 1.7307692307692308, "no_speech_prob": 0.010756919160485268}, {"id": 44, "seek": 15804, "start": 158.04, "end": 164.04, "text": " to make sure that someone hasn't installed something in the hardware or some routines in the firmware.", "tokens": [50364, 281, 652, 988, 300, 1580, 6132, 380, 8899, 746, 294, 264, 8837, 420, 512, 33827, 294, 264, 30289, 13, 50664], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11951127163199492, "compression_ratio": 1.729032258064516, "no_speech_prob": 0.00211882870644331}, {"id": 45, "seek": 15804, "start": 164.04, "end": 170.04, "text": " So hardware is, if you've got a question on that, hardware is where it's most difficult to detect vulnerabilities.", "tokens": [50664, 407, 8837, 307, 11, 498, 291, 600, 658, 257, 1168, 322, 300, 11, 8837, 307, 689, 309, 311, 881, 2252, 281, 5531, 37633, 13, 50964], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11951127163199492, "compression_ratio": 1.729032258064516, "no_speech_prob": 0.00211882870644331}, {"id": 46, "seek": 15804, "start": 170.04, "end": 175.04, "text": " Now when we think about when I say to you, you know, you should secure components,", "tokens": [50964, 823, 562, 321, 519, 466, 562, 286, 584, 281, 291, 11, 291, 458, 11, 291, 820, 7144, 6677, 11, 51214], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11951127163199492, "compression_ratio": 1.729032258064516, "no_speech_prob": 0.00211882870644331}, {"id": 47, "seek": 15804, "start": 175.04, "end": 177.04, "text": " what do I actually mean by that?", "tokens": [51214, 437, 360, 286, 767, 914, 538, 300, 30, 51314], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11951127163199492, "compression_ratio": 1.729032258064516, "no_speech_prob": 0.00211882870644331}, {"id": 48, "seek": 15804, "start": 177.04, "end": 181.04, "text": " And how do you decide what controls to put in place and to what, you know, to what,", "tokens": [51314, 400, 577, 360, 291, 4536, 437, 9003, 281, 829, 294, 1081, 293, 281, 437, 11, 291, 458, 11, 281, 437, 11, 51514], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11951127163199492, "compression_ratio": 1.729032258064516, "no_speech_prob": 0.00211882870644331}, {"id": 49, "seek": 15804, "start": 181.04, "end": 184.04, "text": " how much effort to put into place for controls?", "tokens": [51514, 577, 709, 4630, 281, 829, 666, 1081, 337, 9003, 30, 51664], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11951127163199492, "compression_ratio": 1.729032258064516, "no_speech_prob": 0.00211882870644331}, {"id": 50, "seek": 15804, "start": 184.04, "end": 187.04, "text": " Ultimately what it comes down to is based on organizational relevance.", "tokens": [51664, 23921, 437, 309, 1487, 760, 281, 307, 2361, 322, 24730, 32684, 13, 51814], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11951127163199492, "compression_ratio": 1.729032258064516, "no_speech_prob": 0.00211882870644331}, {"id": 51, "seek": 18704, "start": 187.04, "end": 190.04, "text": " So security controls need to be based on how valuable.", "tokens": [50364, 407, 3825, 9003, 643, 281, 312, 2361, 322, 577, 8263, 13, 50514], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10330223185675484, "compression_ratio": 1.934959349593496, "no_speech_prob": 0.006659016478806734}, {"id": 52, "seek": 18704, "start": 190.04, "end": 194.04, "text": " By the way, that term organizational relevance, what does that really mean?", "tokens": [50514, 3146, 264, 636, 11, 300, 1433, 24730, 32684, 11, 437, 775, 300, 534, 914, 30, 50714], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10330223185675484, "compression_ratio": 1.934959349593496, "no_speech_prob": 0.006659016478806734}, {"id": 53, "seek": 18704, "start": 194.04, "end": 199.04, "text": " Well, it means what does this system, this process do with an organization?", "tokens": [50714, 1042, 11, 309, 1355, 437, 775, 341, 1185, 11, 341, 1399, 360, 365, 364, 4475, 30, 50964], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10330223185675484, "compression_ratio": 1.934959349593496, "no_speech_prob": 0.006659016478806734}, {"id": 54, "seek": 18704, "start": 199.04, "end": 203.04, "text": " What's its organizational relevance, which implies value?", "tokens": [50964, 708, 311, 1080, 24730, 32684, 11, 597, 18779, 2158, 30, 51164], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10330223185675484, "compression_ratio": 1.934959349593496, "no_speech_prob": 0.006659016478806734}, {"id": 55, "seek": 18704, "start": 203.04, "end": 204.04, "text": " Watch out for that in the exam.", "tokens": [51164, 7277, 484, 337, 300, 294, 264, 1139, 13, 51214], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10330223185675484, "compression_ratio": 1.934959349593496, "no_speech_prob": 0.006659016478806734}, {"id": 56, "seek": 18704, "start": 204.04, "end": 209.04, "text": " If you see something that says like organizational relevance, it's implying how valuable the system is.", "tokens": [51214, 759, 291, 536, 746, 300, 1619, 411, 24730, 32684, 11, 309, 311, 704, 7310, 577, 8263, 264, 1185, 307, 13, 51464], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10330223185675484, "compression_ratio": 1.934959349593496, "no_speech_prob": 0.006659016478806734}, {"id": 57, "seek": 18704, "start": 209.04, "end": 213.04, "text": " And so we implement controls based on the value of the system, the process.", "tokens": [51464, 400, 370, 321, 4445, 9003, 2361, 322, 264, 2158, 295, 264, 1185, 11, 264, 1399, 13, 51664], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10330223185675484, "compression_ratio": 1.934959349593496, "no_speech_prob": 0.006659016478806734}, {"id": 58, "seek": 21304, "start": 214.04, "end": 220.04, "text": " Specific to mobile systems, things like cell phones, there's one particular technology that I want to talk about.", "tokens": [50414, 20484, 1089, 281, 6013, 3652, 11, 721, 411, 2815, 10216, 11, 456, 311, 472, 1729, 2899, 300, 286, 528, 281, 751, 466, 13, 50714], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0818029291489545, "compression_ratio": 1.7926829268292683, "no_speech_prob": 0.1128634661436081}, {"id": 59, "seek": 21304, "start": 220.04, "end": 224.04, "text": " And that is MDM mobile device management software.", "tokens": [50714, 400, 300, 307, 22521, 44, 6013, 4302, 4592, 4722, 13, 50914], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0818029291489545, "compression_ratio": 1.7926829268292683, "no_speech_prob": 0.1128634661436081}, {"id": 60, "seek": 21304, "start": 224.04, "end": 226.04, "text": " It's essentially like installing big brother on your phone.", "tokens": [50914, 467, 311, 4476, 411, 20762, 955, 3708, 322, 428, 2593, 13, 51014], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0818029291489545, "compression_ratio": 1.7926829268292683, "no_speech_prob": 0.1128634661436081}, {"id": 61, "seek": 21304, "start": 226.04, "end": 230.04, "text": " It allows a corporation to install a little agent on a device.", "tokens": [51014, 467, 4045, 257, 22197, 281, 3625, 257, 707, 9461, 322, 257, 4302, 13, 51214], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0818029291489545, "compression_ratio": 1.7926829268292683, "no_speech_prob": 0.1128634661436081}, {"id": 62, "seek": 21304, "start": 230.04, "end": 234.04, "text": " The MDM software is an agent that gets installed on an endpoint, like a phone.", "tokens": [51214, 440, 22521, 44, 4722, 307, 364, 9461, 300, 2170, 8899, 322, 364, 35795, 11, 411, 257, 2593, 13, 51414], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0818029291489545, "compression_ratio": 1.7926829268292683, "no_speech_prob": 0.1128634661436081}, {"id": 63, "seek": 21304, "start": 234.04, "end": 239.04, "text": " And then that software agent allows the corporation to monitor the device,", "tokens": [51414, 400, 550, 300, 4722, 9461, 4045, 264, 22197, 281, 6002, 264, 4302, 11, 51664], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0818029291489545, "compression_ratio": 1.7926829268292683, "no_speech_prob": 0.1128634661436081}, {"id": 64, "seek": 23904, "start": 239.04, "end": 242.04, "text": " to implement, to require certain controls.", "tokens": [50364, 281, 4445, 11, 281, 3651, 1629, 9003, 13, 50514], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13130210240681967, "compression_ratio": 1.7269372693726937, "no_speech_prob": 0.03419572860002518}, {"id": 65, "seek": 23904, "start": 242.04, "end": 245.04, "text": " The MDM software, for instance, will enforce whole drive encryption,", "tokens": [50514, 440, 22521, 44, 4722, 11, 337, 5197, 11, 486, 24825, 1379, 3332, 29575, 11, 50664], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13130210240681967, "compression_ratio": 1.7269372693726937, "no_speech_prob": 0.03419572860002518}, {"id": 66, "seek": 23904, "start": 245.04, "end": 248.04, "text": " will enforce strong passwords, things like that.", "tokens": [50664, 486, 24825, 2068, 33149, 11, 721, 411, 300, 13, 50814], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13130210240681967, "compression_ratio": 1.7269372693726937, "no_speech_prob": 0.03419572860002518}, {"id": 67, "seek": 23904, "start": 248.04, "end": 250.04, "text": " And even things like remote white.", "tokens": [50814, 400, 754, 721, 411, 8607, 2418, 13, 50914], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13130210240681967, "compression_ratio": 1.7269372693726937, "no_speech_prob": 0.03419572860002518}, {"id": 68, "seek": 23904, "start": 250.04, "end": 252.04, "text": " So that's MDM software.", "tokens": [50914, 407, 300, 311, 22521, 44, 4722, 13, 51014], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13130210240681967, "compression_ratio": 1.7269372693726937, "no_speech_prob": 0.03419572860002518}, {"id": 69, "seek": 23904, "start": 252.04, "end": 257.03999999999996, "text": " And it can even go to the point of if a device isn't in compliance.", "tokens": [51014, 400, 309, 393, 754, 352, 281, 264, 935, 295, 498, 257, 4302, 1943, 380, 294, 15882, 13, 51264], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13130210240681967, "compression_ratio": 1.7269372693726937, "no_speech_prob": 0.03419572860002518}, {"id": 70, "seek": 23904, "start": 257.03999999999996, "end": 260.03999999999996, "text": " And this is used a lot where organizations allow BYOD or CYOD", "tokens": [51264, 400, 341, 307, 1143, 257, 688, 689, 6150, 2089, 26930, 14632, 420, 383, 56, 14632, 51414], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13130210240681967, "compression_ratio": 1.7269372693726937, "no_speech_prob": 0.03419572860002518}, {"id": 71, "seek": 23904, "start": 260.03999999999996, "end": 262.03999999999996, "text": " bring your own device, carry your own device.", "tokens": [51414, 1565, 428, 1065, 4302, 11, 3985, 428, 1065, 4302, 13, 51514], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13130210240681967, "compression_ratio": 1.7269372693726937, "no_speech_prob": 0.03419572860002518}, {"id": 72, "seek": 23904, "start": 262.03999999999996, "end": 266.03999999999996, "text": " If an organization is allowing people to bring in their personal phones,", "tokens": [51514, 759, 364, 4475, 307, 8293, 561, 281, 1565, 294, 641, 2973, 10216, 11, 51714], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13130210240681967, "compression_ratio": 1.7269372693726937, "no_speech_prob": 0.03419572860002518}, {"id": 73, "seek": 26604, "start": 266.04, "end": 269.04, "text": " it's a very good idea to install this MDM software on those devices,", "tokens": [50364, 309, 311, 257, 588, 665, 1558, 281, 3625, 341, 22521, 44, 4722, 322, 729, 5759, 11, 50514], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0873785374769524, "compression_ratio": 1.7009345794392523, "no_speech_prob": 0.008267117664217949}, {"id": 74, "seek": 26604, "start": 269.04, "end": 273.04, "text": " to make sure that those devices are secure before they're allowed to connect to", "tokens": [50514, 281, 652, 988, 300, 729, 5759, 366, 7144, 949, 436, 434, 4350, 281, 1745, 281, 50714], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0873785374769524, "compression_ratio": 1.7009345794392523, "no_speech_prob": 0.008267117664217949}, {"id": 75, "seek": 26604, "start": 273.04, "end": 277.04, "text": " and obtain information from the corporate network.", "tokens": [50714, 293, 12701, 1589, 490, 264, 10896, 3209, 13, 50914], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0873785374769524, "compression_ratio": 1.7009345794392523, "no_speech_prob": 0.008267117664217949}, {"id": 76, "seek": 26604, "start": 277.04, "end": 279.04, "text": " Now, a final piece I want to talk about here.", "tokens": [50914, 823, 11, 257, 2572, 2522, 286, 528, 281, 751, 466, 510, 13, 51014], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0873785374769524, "compression_ratio": 1.7009345794392523, "no_speech_prob": 0.008267117664217949}, {"id": 77, "seek": 26604, "start": 279.04, "end": 283.04, "text": " And this is applied to whenever you want to protect any sort of system.", "tokens": [51014, 400, 341, 307, 6456, 281, 5699, 291, 528, 281, 2371, 604, 1333, 295, 1185, 13, 51214], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0873785374769524, "compression_ratio": 1.7009345794392523, "no_speech_prob": 0.008267117664217949}, {"id": 78, "seek": 26604, "start": 283.04, "end": 285.04, "text": " You go through this process of hardening.", "tokens": [51214, 509, 352, 807, 341, 1399, 295, 1152, 4559, 13, 51314], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0873785374769524, "compression_ratio": 1.7009345794392523, "no_speech_prob": 0.008267117664217949}, {"id": 79, "seek": 26604, "start": 285.04, "end": 287.04, "text": " And we've talked about this a couple times now, right?", "tokens": [51314, 400, 321, 600, 2825, 466, 341, 257, 1916, 1413, 586, 11, 558, 30, 51414], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0873785374769524, "compression_ratio": 1.7009345794392523, "no_speech_prob": 0.008267117664217949}, {"id": 80, "seek": 26604, "start": 287.04, "end": 291.04, "text": " It's this concept of going through a device, looking very carefully at the configuration,", "tokens": [51414, 467, 311, 341, 3410, 295, 516, 807, 257, 4302, 11, 1237, 588, 7500, 412, 264, 11694, 11, 51614], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0873785374769524, "compression_ratio": 1.7009345794392523, "no_speech_prob": 0.008267117664217949}, {"id": 81, "seek": 26604, "start": 291.04, "end": 293.04, "text": " making sure all the patches are in place,", "tokens": [51614, 1455, 988, 439, 264, 26531, 366, 294, 1081, 11, 51714], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.0873785374769524, "compression_ratio": 1.7009345794392523, "no_speech_prob": 0.008267117664217949}, {"id": 82, "seek": 29304, "start": 293.04, "end": 298.04, "text": " disabling unnecessary services, installing the appropriate security controls", "tokens": [50364, 717, 20112, 19350, 3328, 11, 20762, 264, 6854, 3825, 9003, 50614], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10695916598605126, "compression_ratio": 1.5568627450980392, "no_speech_prob": 0.010515318252146244}, {"id": 83, "seek": 29304, "start": 298.04, "end": 301.04, "text": " like anti-mower, host-based firewall, host-based IDS IPS.", "tokens": [50614, 411, 6061, 12, 76, 968, 11, 3975, 12, 6032, 36109, 11, 3975, 12, 6032, 7348, 50, 50021, 13, 50764], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10695916598605126, "compression_ratio": 1.5568627450980392, "no_speech_prob": 0.010515318252146244}, {"id": 84, "seek": 29304, "start": 301.04, "end": 307.04, "text": " It's going through a checklist and locking down any type of device.", "tokens": [50764, 467, 311, 516, 807, 257, 30357, 293, 23954, 760, 604, 2010, 295, 4302, 13, 51064], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10695916598605126, "compression_ratio": 1.5568627450980392, "no_speech_prob": 0.010515318252146244}, {"id": 85, "seek": 29304, "start": 307.04, "end": 311.04, "text": " And this concept of hardening absolutely applies to how you secure a mobile device,", "tokens": [51064, 400, 341, 3410, 295, 1152, 4559, 3122, 13165, 281, 577, 291, 7144, 257, 6013, 4302, 11, 51264], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10695916598605126, "compression_ratio": 1.5568627450980392, "no_speech_prob": 0.010515318252146244}, {"id": 86, "seek": 29304, "start": 311.04, "end": 314.04, "text": " a laptop, a server.", "tokens": [51264, 257, 10732, 11, 257, 7154, 13, 51414], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10695916598605126, "compression_ratio": 1.5568627450980392, "no_speech_prob": 0.010515318252146244}, {"id": 87, "seek": 29304, "start": 314.04, "end": 319.04, "text": " So there you go. That's how you do a better job of addressing vulnerabilities and systems.", "tokens": [51414, 407, 456, 291, 352, 13, 663, 311, 577, 291, 360, 257, 1101, 1691, 295, 14329, 37633, 293, 3652, 13, 51664], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.10695916598605126, "compression_ratio": 1.5568627450980392, "no_speech_prob": 0.010515318252146244}], "language": "en"}